     <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION:GOVERNMENT">Resolution Funding Corp.</ENAMEX> , known as <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION:GOVERNMENT">Refcorp</ENAMEX> , a <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC:GOVERNMENT">division</ENAMEX> of a new government <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC:GOVERNMENT">agency</ENAMEX> created to bail out the <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE_DESC:COUNTRY">nation</ENAMEX> 's troubled savings and loan <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC:CORPORATION">associations</ENAMEX> , will hold its <NUMEX TYPE="ORDINAL">first</NUMEX> bond auction <TIMEX TYPE="DATE:DATE">Wednesday</TIMEX> , when it will sell <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">$ 4.5 billion</NUMEX> of <TIMEX TYPE="DATE:DURATION">30-year</TIMEX> bonds .
